<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hi All,</p> <p>Inspired by Emacs From Scratch I decided to upend my IDE functionality in my config for lsp-mode. LSP starts and is functional, but lsp-ui is shoddy. The sideline functionality and the header breadcrumbs do not work. For me this is not a big deal, but what is bothering me is that lsp-ui-flycheck-list does not work. I need to manually run M-x load-library lsp-ui-flycheck and only then will lsp-ui-flycheck-list show me the list of errors on the page. This leads me to believe there is a loading issue somewhere.</p> <p>the relevant init section is this:</p> <p>``` (use-package lsp-mode :straight t :commands lsp :hook ((typescript-mode js2-mode web-mode python-mode) . lsp) :bind (:map lsp-mode-map (&quot;TAB&quot; . completion-at-point)) :custom (lsp-headerline-breadcrumb-enable nil))</p> <p>(use-package lsp-ui :straight t :hook (lsp-mode . lsp-ui-mode) :config (setq lsp-ui-sideline-enable t) (setq lsp-ui-sideline-show-hover nil) (setq lsp-ui-doc-position &#39;bottom) (lsp-ui-doc-show))</p> <p>(use-package lsp-treemacs :after lsp)</p> <p>```</p> <p>After startup I do see a few relevant error messages:</p> <p>``` ... File mode specification error: (error The connected server(s) does not support method textDocument/hover. To find out what capabilities support your server use ‘M-x lsp-describe-session’ and expand the capabilities section) Error running timer: (error &quot;The connected server(s) does not support method textDocument/hover. To find out what capabilities support your server use ‘M-x lsp-describe-session’ and expand the capabilities section&quot;) LSP :: pylsp:11352 initialized successfully in folders: ...</p> <p>``` Can this be the source of the problem ?</p> <p>thx. S</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Sndr666"> /u/Sndr666 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/scg0nz/lspui_fails_to_initialize_but_gives_no_error_on/">[link]</a></span